Filename: ./pool/cython3-legacy_0.29.36-3_arm64.deb
Size: 1737884
MD5sum: 032f390afff21b81488a4bbbfb264056
SHA1: 5dfc9d14de960299708341d4164fbca1a47b79f9
SHA256: b1bf52adc65f057e4752f1dd389f66c324543b8c0426a6c1a80ff751dbc65935
Section: python
Priority: optional
Homepage: http://cython.org/
Description: C-Extensions for Python 3 (legacy version 0.29)
 Cython is a language that makes writing C extensions for the Python language as
 easy as Python itself. Cython is based on the well-known Pyrex, but supports
 more cutting edge functionality and optimizations.
 .
 The Cython language is very close to the Python language, but Cython
 additionally supports calling C functions and declaring C types on variables
 and class attributes. This allows the compiler to generate very efficient C
 code from Cython code.
 .
 This makes Cython the ideal language for wrapping external C libraries, and
 for fast C modules that speed up the execution of Python code.
 .
 This legacy version may not work with Python 3.12.  In particular, the
 pyximport module appears to fail.  This legacy version should not be used
 as a package run-time dependency.

